52:53.036 --> 52:55.561
<i>"...against the Panther...</i>

52:55.672 --> 52:59.267
and they went off to look
for Kaa the Rock Python.

53:01.811 --> 53:06.646
They found him stretched out
on a warm ledge in the afternoon sun...

53:06.750 --> 53:09.241
admiring his beautiful new coat."

53:18.962 --> 53:20.930
Who do you love the most?

53:26.303 --> 53:28.737
I love you all three the same.

53:30.473 --> 53:33.442
Tell us a story from before we can remember.

53:37.314 --> 53:39.282
Went for a ride in a plane once.

53:43.053 --> 53:45.351
<i>It was a graduation present.</i>

54:00.870 --> 54:02.497
<i>Mother.</i>

54:11.214 --> 54:13.114
<i>Make me good.</i>

54:20.657 --> 54:22.284
<i>Brave.</i>

55:41.838 --> 55:45.001
Aah! Aah!

57:21.538 --> 57:23.870
<i>Can it happen to anyone?</i>

57:24.908 --> 57:26.535
Shh.

57:30.513 --> 57:32.640
<i>Nobody talks about it.</i>

57:37.053 --> 57:38.816
<i>Help me not to sass my dad.</i>

57:41.391 --> 57:44.485
Help me not to get dogs in fights.

57:58.741 --> 58:01.710
Help me be thankful
for everything I've got.

58:03.847 --> 58:05.974
<i>Where do you live?</i>

58:07.016 --> 58:08.813
Help me not to tell lies.

58:16.559 --> 58:18.857
<i>Are you watching me?</i>

58:28.838 --> 58:30.965
<i>I want to know what you are.</i>

58:37.647 --> 58:40.172
<i>I want to see what you see.</i>

59:32.935 --> 59:35.233
<i>Come here, you!</i>

59:35.338 --> 59:38.330
Come here. Come here, you!

59:40.376 --> 59:42.139
That funny?

59:48.317 --> 59:51.980
You're gonna stand there, and you're
gonna close this door quietly 50 times.

59:53.423 --> 59:55.914
Count it out.

59:56.025 --> 59:59.085
Three, four...

59:59.195 --> 01:00:01.993
<i>five, six...</i>

01:00:02.098 --> 01:00:04.760
<i>seven, eight-</i>

01:00:04.867 --> 01:00:08.359
You can't just yank off the top.
You gotta get it by the root.

01:00:16.179 --> 01:00:18.147
- <i>Your mother's naive.</i>
- Whoa!

01:00:18.247 --> 01:00:21.045
<i>It takes fierce will
to get ahead in this world.</i>

01:00:22.685 --> 01:00:25.313
<i>If you're good,
people take advantage of you.</i>

01:00:31.727 --> 01:00:35.163
<i>Every one of these top executives-
you know how they got where they are?</i>

01:00:35.264 --> 01:00:38.825
<i>Floated right down
the middle of the river.</i>

01:00:40.236 --> 01:00:43.672
<i>Don't let anyone tell you
there's anything you can't do.</i>

01:00:45.508 --> 01:00:48.477
Don't do like I did.
Promise me that.

01:00:50.546 --> 01:00:52.514
I dreamed of being a great musician.

01:00:53.549 --> 01:00:56.985
I let myself get sidetracked.

01:00:57.086 --> 01:00:59.782
If you're lookin' for somethin' to happen,
that was it.

01:00:59.889 --> 01:01:01.584
That was life. You lived it.

01:01:18.474 --> 01:01:22.570
<i>Job imagined he might build
his nest on high...</i>

01:01:22.678 --> 01:01:27.411
<i>that the integrity of his behavior
would protect him against misfortune.</i>

01:01:27.517 --> 01:01:29.417
<i>And his friends thought, mistakenly...</i>

01:01:29.519 --> 01:01:32.249
that the Lord could only have punished him...

01:01:32.355 --> 01:01:35.950
because secretly he'd done something wrong.

01:01:36.058 --> 01:01:37.548
But no.

01:01:37.660 --> 01:01:41.187
Misfortune befalls the good as well.

01:01:41.297 --> 01:01:43.458
We can't protect ourselves against it.

01:01:43.566 --> 01:01:46.034
We can't protect our children.

01:01:46.135 --> 01:01:48.968
We can't say to ourselves,
"Even if I'm not happy...

01:01:49.071 --> 01:01:51.801
I'm going to make sure they are."

01:01:51.908 --> 01:01:53.808
We run before the wind.

01:01:53.910 --> 01:01:56.640
We think that it will carry us forever.

01:01:56.746 --> 01:01:58.270
It will not.

01:01:58.381 --> 01:02:00.212
We vanish as a cloud.

01:02:00.316 --> 01:02:02.580
We wither as the autumn grass...

01:02:02.685 --> 01:02:05.950
and, like a tree, are rooted up.

01:02:08.090 --> 01:02:11.321
Is there some fraud
in the scheme of the universe?

01:02:11.427 --> 01:02:13.793
Is there nothing which is deathless...

01:02:13.896 --> 01:02:16.797
nothing which does not pass away?

01:02:18.935 --> 01:02:21.130
<i>We cannot stay where we are.</i>

01:02:21.237 --> 01:02:23.501
<i>We must journey forth.</i>

01:02:23.606 --> 01:02:28.043
<i>We must find that which is greater
than fortune or fate.</i>

01:02:29.078 --> 01:02:32.241
<i>Nothing can bring us peace but that.</i>

01:02:33.349 --> 01:02:36.512
<i>Is the body of the wise man
or the just...</i>

01:02:36.619 --> 01:02:38.519
<i>exempt from any pain...</i>

01:02:38.621 --> 01:02:40.714
<i>from any disquietude...</i>

01:02:40.823 --> 01:02:43.553
<i>from the deformity
that might blight its beauty...</i>

01:02:43.659 --> 01:02:46.787
<i>from the weakness
that might destroy its health?</i>

01:02:48.898 --> 01:02:51.731
<i>Do you trust in God?</i>

01:02:51.834 --> 01:02:55.565
<i>Job, too, was close to the Lord.</i>

01:02:55.671 --> 01:02:58.333
<i>Are your friends and children your security?</i>

01:02:59.875 --> 01:03:02.105
<i>There is no hiding place
in all the world...</i>

01:03:02.211 --> 01:03:04.475
<i>where trouble may not find you.</i>

01:03:04.580 --> 01:03:07.344
<i>No one knows when sorrow
might visit his house...</i>

01:03:07.450 --> 01:03:10.544
<i>any more than Job did.</i>

01:03:10.653 --> 01:03:13.781
<i>The very moment everything
was taken away from Job...</i>

01:03:13.889 --> 01:03:17.017
<i>he knew it was the Lord
who'd taken it away.</i>

01:03:19.261 --> 01:03:22.253
<i>He turned from the passing shows of time.</i>

01:03:22.365 --> 01:03:24.799
<i>He sought that which is eternal.</i>

01:03:26.235 --> 01:03:30.569
<i>Does he alone see God's hand
who sees that he gives?</i>

01:03:30.673 --> 01:03:32.698
<i>Or does not, also,
the one see God's hand-</i>

01:03:32.808 --> 01:03:36.300
- I'm your man.
- <i>who sees that he takes away?</i>

01:03:36.412 --> 01:03:38.880
<i>Or does he alone see God...</i>

01:03:38.981 --> 01:03:41.142
<i>who sees God turn his face towards him?</i>

01:03:43.152 --> 01:03:46.713
<i>Does not, also, he see God...</i>

01:03:46.822 --> 01:03:48.449
<i>who sees God turn his back?</i>

